The Kano State Government has ordered the immediate closure of a private school, Noble Kids Academy, at Kwanar Dakata, in the Nassarawa Local Government Area, where the body of five-year-old, Hanifa Abubakar, was buried by the suspects. The deceased was allegedly abducted in November 2021, by her teacher, Abdulmalik, who is a principal suspect in the crime, according to the police. The State Commissioner for Education, Muhammad Kiru, who announced the closure of the school in a statement expressing sadness over the incident, said apart from the closure of the school, the state government would commence the investigation of unregistered private schools and teachers to check such criminal activities. Martinez Pens Long Term Aston Villa Contract Democratic Principles Must Guide Democratic Choices –… He however appealed to parents whose children attend the private school to stop them from doing so pending the completion of the investigation. 